        "GPR-aware scoring, using the biological meaning of gene-protein-reaction (GPR) rules:\n",
        "\n",
        "- AND relationships (enzyme subunits): all subunits are required → the minimum expression is the bottleneck.\n",
        "- OR relationships (isozymes): any isoform is sufficient → the maximum expression counts.\n",
        "\n",
        "The evaluate_gpr helper below walks the GPR parse tree from COBRApy and applies min/max logic recursively, mirroring the standard approach described in:\n",
        "\n",
        "Becker & Palsson (2008) GIMME; Frontera et al. (2022) Frontiers in Oncology."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 12,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "oAsOWq6UCT7c",
