        "### 2.7: Flux Variability Analysis (FVA)\n",
        "\n",
        "Address alternate-optima uncertainty with FVA. A single GIMME solution is one of potentially many equivalent flux distributions. FVA characterises the full feasible range for each reaction at 90% of the GIMME objective value, quantifying which reactions are robustly different between conditions versus which are just artefacts of the specific solver path taken.\n",
        "\n",
        "Only reactions whose FVA ranges do not overlap between conditions are treated as confidently differentially active.\n",
        "\n",
        "Reference: Mahadevan & Schilling (2003) Metabolic Engineering; Gudmundsson & Thiele (2010) BMC Bioinformatics."
      ]
    },
